en, J., Brosofske, K.D., Naiman, R.J., Modelling air temperature gradients across managed small streams in western Washington (1998) J. Environ. Manage., 53, pp. 309-321; Dosdall, L.M., Lehmkuhl, D.M., The nymph of Utacapnia trava (Nebeker and Gaufin) (Plecoptera: Capniidae) (1988) Pan-Pac. Entomol., 64, pp. 353-357; Enders, G., Wagner, R., Mortality of Apatania fimbriata (Insecta: Trichoptera) during embryonic, larval and adult life stages (1996) Freshwater Biol., 36, pp. 93-104; Erelli, M.C., Matthew, P.A., Eaton, G.K., Altitudinal patterns in host suitability for forest (1998) Oecologia, 117, pp. 133-142. , Berl; Fleishman, E., Launer, A.E., Weiss, S.B., Reed, J.M., Boggs, C.L., Murphy, D.D., Finch, R.R., (1990) Longevity, Senescence and the Genome, , University of Chicago Press, Chicago, IL; Griffith, M.B., Barrows, E.M., Perry, S.A., Lateral dispersal of adult aquatic insects (Plecoptera, Trichoptera) following emergence from headwater streams in forested Appalachian catchments (1998) Ecol. Populat. Biol., 91, pp. 195-201; Harker, J.E., The structure of the foregut and midgut of nymphs, subimagos and imagos of Cloeon dipterum (Ephemeroptera) and the functions of the gut of adult mayflies (1999) J. Zool. Lond., 248, pp. 243-253; Hogg, I.D., Williams, D.D., Response of stream invertebrates to a global-warming thermal regime: An ecosystem-level manipulation (1996) Ecology, 77, pp. 395-407; Hogg, I.D., Williams, D.D., Eadie, J.M., Butt, S.A., The consequences of global warming from stream invertebrates: A field simulation (1995) J. Therm. Biol., 20, pp. 199-206; Hogg, I.D., Eadie, J.M., De Lafontaine, Y., Atmospheric change and the diversity of aquatic invertebrates: Are we missing the boat? (1998) Environ. Manage. Monit., 49, pp. 291-301; Hogg, I.D., Willmann-Heurner, P., Stevens, M.I., Population genetic structure of two New Zealand stream insects: Archichauliodes diversus (Megaloptera) and Coloburiscus humeralis (Ephemeroptera) (2002) N.Z.J. Mar. Freshwater Res.